        "timestamp": 1765140100
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It looks Artie might mean the sequence for a given Sylow subgroup?</p>",
        "id": 562343002,
        "sender_full_name": "Ya√´l Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1765141146
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's not unique either (it could be a vector space over Z/pZ for example). Every \"the\" in the last sentence of Artie's post is confusing.</p>",
        "id": 562348061,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1765142383
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah it's not unique in any way<br>\nI just mean, do we have some sequence of those groups packaged together</p>",
        "id": 562363870,
        "sender_full_name": "Artie Khovanov",
        "timestamp": 1765146241
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But it's moot because I realised in my application I only need to go two steps so I can just apply the lemma twice</p>",
        "id": 562363953,
        "sender_full_name": "Artie Khovanov",
        "timestamp": 1765146265
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I just remembered that this amounts to a composition series for a Sylow p-group, but I don‚Äôt know if we have existence of composition series.</p>",
        "id": 562559422,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Carnahan",
        "timestamp": 1765228526
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Found 0 declarations mentioning CompositionSeries and Group.</code><br>\nlooks like no</p>",
        "id": 562559822,
        "sender_full_name": "Artie Khovanov",
        "timestamp": 1765228664
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See <br>\n<a class=\"message-link\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Composition.20Series.20for.20Groups.20wrt.20Normal.20subgroup/near/503509845\">#Is there code for X? &gt; Composition Series for Groups wrt Normal subgroup @ üí¨</a> <br>\n<a class=\"message-link\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/116395-maths/topic/JordanHolderLattice.20for.20Subgroup/near/520894899\">#maths &gt; JordanHolderLattice for Subgroup @ üí¨</a></p>",
        "id": 562561374,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1765229311
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am pretty sure this is about uniqueness and I am asking about existence.<br>\nAnd moreover I'm not just asking for <em>any</em> series; I want a series where all the indexes are <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span>. There's some content here (that follows from the theorem I linked).</p>",
        "id": 562561789,
        "sender_full_name": "Artie Khovanov",
        "timestamp": 1765229491
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A series where all the indexes are <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span> is precisely a composition series.</p>",
        "id": 562562762,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1765229902
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, and composition series are not unique, though the multiset of successive quotients is unique up to isomorphisms.</p>",
        "id": 562563403,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1765230182
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't disagree <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110038\">@Kevin Buzzard</span><br>\nBut the statement that was linked only talks about maximality<br>\nWhen what I want is precisely that the maximal subgroup has index <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span>!</p>",
        "id": 562564518,
        "sender_full_name": "Artie Khovanov",
        "timestamp": 1765230648
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And yeah by uniqueness I meant the quotient thing</p>",
        "id": 562564585,
        "sender_full_name": "Artie Khovanov",
        "timestamp": 1765230685
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>H being a maximal normal subgroup in K means that K/H is simple, and a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span>-group is simple iff it is cyclic.</p>\n<p>There is <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Order/RelSeries.html#LTSeries.exists_relSeries_covBy\">LTSeries.exists_relSeries_covBy</a> but CovBy is maximality without normality, so you'll need to prove something harder, see <a href=\"https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/1763518/every-proper-maximal-subgroup-of-a-p-group-p-is-normal-and-has-index-p\">https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/1763518/every-proper-maximal-subgroup-of-a-p-group-p-is-normal-and-has-index-p</a></p>\n<p>It's probably easier to build a LTSeries from <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/GroupTheory/Sylow.html#Sylow.exists_subgroup_card_pow_succ\">Sylow.exists_subgroup_card_pow_succ</a> by recursion.</p>",
        "id": 562567749,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1765232020
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, quite</p>",
